<HEADLINE>
KAOHSIUNG INTERNATIONAL TRAVEL FAIR TO OPEN MAY 3
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  May 1 (CNA) 05/01/07  18:51:54 (By Luis Huang)
</P>
<P>
The 2007 Kaohsiung International Travel Fair is scheduled to be
held May 3-6 at the Kaohsiung Business Exhibition Center under
the auspices of the Kaohsiung Association of Travel agents,
during which tens of thousands of people are expected to visit
the fair to hunt for bargain tour packages.
</P>
<P>
Huang Chin-hsiang, deputy chairman of the fair's organizing
committee, told a news conference that Vice President Annette Lu,
who has spared no efforts to help promote Taiwan's tourism
industry, has promised to cut the ribbon at an opening ceremony
slated for May 3.
</P>
<P>
Huang said that the organizers are inviting the three other
candidates vying for ruling Democratic Progressive Party's 2008
presidential nomination, but added that DPP Chairman Yu Shyi-kun
has declined the invitation due to his tight schedule.
</P>
<P>
Among those taking part in the fair will be local governments
from around the country, local travel agencies, hotel operators,
foreign tourism organizations, as well as domestic and foreign
theme parks and other travel-related sectors, Huang said, adding
that the Polish and Indian representative offices will also
attend the fair for the first time.
</P>
<P>
During the three-day exhibition, a total of 318 booths will be
set up to attract prospective tourists, including 39 booths by
foreign tourism institutions in Taiwan and 190 booths
representing local amusement areas, according to Huang.
</P>
